### ReadCollectionFilterParameters() `method`

##### Summary

Reads parameters of collection filter methods from JSON.
If the method name doesn't have explicit type descriptions, it will fallback to the default implementation, which support simple property types like string, boolean, integer.
A method name can carry additional parameter type description, which is used to deserialize parameters correctly.  For example ProjectsByProjectGuid(guid[]) allows the function
to create an array of guid. Without that, it will be coverted to string[], because Guids are written to strings inside JSON.

##### Parameters

This method has no parameters.

## IAsyncQueryDefinition `type`

##### Namespace

Microsoft.VisualStudio.ProjectSystem.Query.Providers

##### Summary

Information inside [AsyncQueryable](#T-Microsoft-VisualStudio-ProjectSystem-Query-AsyncQueryable 'Microsoft.VisualStudio.ProjectSystem.Query.AsyncQueryable') to pass to the [IQueryByRelationshipDataProvider2](#T-Microsoft-VisualStudio-ProjectSystem-Query-Providers-IQueryByRelationshipDataProvider2 'Microsoft.VisualStudio.ProjectSystem.Query.Providers.IQueryByRelationshipDataProvider2') to create runtime data provider.
The reason we don't pass [AsyncQueryable](#T-Microsoft-VisualStudio-ProjectSystem-Query-AsyncQueryable 'Microsoft.VisualStudio.ProjectSystem.Query.AsyncQueryable') to the provider directly is that we have strong type query for local queries and weak type one for remote queries.
It would be too easy for a provider to depend on strong type contract without realizing it won't work for remote queries.

<a name='T-Microsoft-VisualStudio-ProjectSystem-Query-IProjectSystemQueryService'></a>
## IProjectSystemQueryService `type`

##### Namespace

Microsoft.VisualStudio.ProjectSystem.Query

##### Summary

The entry point to use the project system query APIs. It is exposed as a service inside VS.
From here, a client can get the root queryable workspace to retrieve project system data.
Note: when a major change impacting the entire object space happens, (for example, client is disconnected from Nexus server),
the original [IProjectModelQueryableSpace](#T-Microsoft-VisualStudio-ProjectSystem-Query-IProjectModelQueryableSpace 'Microsoft.VisualStudio.ProjectSystem.Query.IProjectModelQueryableSpace') will be disposed (and firing notification before that.)
A client is expected to retrieve a new workspace when the client connects to a new server (or opens a solution locally, in which case
it will use a server side workspace object).
